h4. Problem Statement:

I am trying to see if we have a Bitbucket REST API call which will provide commit ID information for a file in a branch

I was able to use the below end point if the file exists in default master branch but unable to construct one for a file residing in a branch
{code:java}
curl -k -X GET -u username:password https://bitbucket-server-instance/bitbucket/rest/api/1.0/projects/PROJ/repos/test-repo/commits/&#63;path=test.yml
{code}
But doesn't seem to work for a non-default branch.
h4. Suggested resolution:

Have a API which can add the filename and it would provide the Commit ID of that file.
{code:java}
/REST/API/1.0/PROJECTS/{PROJECTKEY}/REPOS/{REPOSITORYSLUG}/branch/COMMITS?File&path
{code}

Calling large pull request diff rest endpoint in a browser or using curl returns truncated json
{code:java}
https://<bb server>/rest/api/1.0/projects/<project>/repos/<repo>/pull-requests/<num>/diff
{code}
Workaround from BSERV-5429 (-http1.0) is not working.

Gravatar can be disabled in the UI. This sets avatar.source to disabled in app_property:
{code:sql}
select * from app_property where prop_key = 'avatar.source';
{code}
This property should also be able to be set in [Bitbucket Server config properties|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bitbucketserver/bitbucket-server-config-properties-776640155.html#BitbucketServerconfigproperties-Avatars] file. The setting in [Bitbucket Server config properties|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bitbucketserver/bitbucket-server-config-properties-776640155.html#BitbucketServerconfigproperties-Avatars] should overwrite all other configurations. This makes it easier to disable programmatically and allow an audit to confirm that Gravatar is disabled.

We have a Bitbucket server with a repo containing a file in this folder:

shared/datatypes/src/main/java/com/compuware/apm/datatypes/api/uem/VisualCompleteAdditionalData.java

with content:
{noformat}
...
public class VisualCompleteAdditionalData {
...
{noformat}

so together with the documentation:
https://confluence.atlassian.com/bitbucketserver064/search-for-code-in-bitbucket-server-974388871.html?utm_campaign=in-app-help&utm_medium=in-app-help&utm_source=stash
{quote}
A query in Bitbucket has to contain at least one search term, which can either be a single word or a phrase surrounded by quotes.
{quote}

I would expect when searching for "class VisualCompleteAdditionalData" (incl quotes) to find this file with this content. However:
{quote}We couldn't find any results matching
project:RX repo:cluster "class VisualCompleteAdditionalData"
{quote}
